timeClock

Class Clock

  • java.lang.Object
    • timeClock.Clock

  • public class Clock
extends java.lang.Object
    Clock class. Contains methods that convert time units into hourly earnings. This is handles most of the back-end calculating for the Time Clock.
    Author:
    Tyler Hay, Freeman Ogburn, Max Jensen

      • calcTime

        public double calcTime(int time1H,
                       int time1M,
                       int time1AMPM,
                       int time2H,
                       int time2M,
                       int time2AMPM)
        the calcTime method takes in the "clock-in" time, and the "clock-out" time in hour, minute, and AM/PM sections. The method takes the difference between the two times to calculate the total time worked for the day. How the difference is calculated is based on the AM/PM of each time to make sure the calculated time difference is within the typical 24-hour day time schedule.
        Parameters:
        time1H - Integer of hour clocked-in
        time1M - Integer of minute clock-in
        time1AMPM - Integer representing AM or PM. 0 = AM and 1 = PM.
        time2H - Integer of hour clocked-out
        time2M - Integer of minute clocked-out
        time2AMPM - Integer representing AM or PM. 0 = AM and 1 = PM.
        Returns:
        Double vale of total time worked
